                              "children": {
                                "8": {
                                  "id": "8",
                                  "speaker": "Player",
                                  "text": "Go ahead, Gale. I'm listening.",
                                  "context": "NodeContext: Knows exactly what he's talking about, giving clear direction (important - player will have to follow it)",
                                  "checkflags": [],
                                  "setflags": [],
                                  "ruletags": [],
                                  "approval": [],
                                  "rolls": "",
                                  "goto": "",
                                  "link": "",
                                  "is_end": false,
                                  "node_type": "normal",
                                  "children": {
                                    "31": {
                                      "id": "31",
                                      "speaker": "Gale",
                                      "text": "First, move your white queen to the upper right corner. Then, move her four squares to the left.",
                                      "context": "NodeContext: Knows exactly what he's talking about, giving clear direction (important - player will have to follow it)",
                                      "checkflags": [
                                        "WYR_Chess_State_Option1"
                                      ],
                                      "setflags": [],
                                      "ruletags": [],
                                      "approval": [],
                                      "rolls": "",
                                      "goto": "",
                                      "link": "",
                                      "is_end": false,
                                      "node_type": "normal",
                                      "children": {
                                        "3": {
                                          "id": "3",
                                          "speaker": "Gale",
                                          "text": "The king can only withdraw to one square after the first move, and after the second has nowhere to retreat.",
                                          "context": "",
                                          "checkflags": [],
                                          "setflags": [
                                            "WYR_Chess_Knows_HeardGalesSolution"
                                          ],
                                          "ruletags": [],
                                          "approval": [],
                                          "rolls": "",
                                          "goto": "",
                                          "link": "",
                                          "is_end": true,
                                          "node_type": "normal",
                                          "children": {}
                                        }
                                      }
                                    },
                                    "13": {
                                      "id": "13",
                                      "speaker": "Gale",
                                      "text": "First, have the white queen move all the way across and capture the black pawn. This leaves black's king in check, forcing him to retreat a square left.",
                                      "context": "NodeContext: Knows exactly what he's talking about, giving clear direction (important - player will have to follow it)",
                                      "checkflags": [
                                        "WYR_Chess_State_Option2"
                                      ],
                                      "setflags": [],
                                      "ruletags": [],
                                      "approval": [],
                                      "rolls": "",
                                      "goto": "",
                                      "link": "",
                                      "is_end": false,
                                      "node_type": "normal",
                                      "children": {
                                        "21": {
                                          "id": "21",
                                          "speaker": "Gale",
                                          "text": "Your queen then takes the other pawn, one square up and left, always under the protection of her faithful bishop.",
                                          "context": "NodeContext: Knows exactly what he's talking about, giving clear direction (important - player will have to follow it)",
                                          "checkflags": [],
                                          "setflags": [
                                            "WYR_Chess_Knows_HeardGalesSolution"
                                          ],
                                          "ruletags": [],
                                          "approval": [],
                                          "rolls": "",
                                          "goto": "",
                                          "link": "",
                                          "is_end": true,
                                          "node_type": "normal",
                                          "children": {}
                                        }
                                      }
                                    },
                                    "27": {
                                      "id": "27",
                                      "speaker": "Gale",
                                      "text": "First, threaten the black king. Move your rook one square to the right. That leaves black only two choices:",
                                      "context": "NodeContext: Knows exactly what he's talking about, giving clear direction (important - player will have to follow it)",
                                      "checkflags": [
                                        "WYR_Chess_State_Option3"
                                      ],
                                      "setflags": [],
                                      "ruletags": [],
                                      "approval": [],
                                      "rolls": "",
                                      "goto": "",
                                      "link": "",
                                      "is_end": false,
                                      "node_type": "normal",
                                      "children": {
                                        "10": {
                                          "id": "10",
                                          "speaker": "Gale",
                                          "text": "Option one - the black bishop can take your rook. This leaves your queen free to move three squares to the right, and checkmate black's king, your knight pinning him down.",
                                          "context": "NodeContext: Knows exactly what he's talking about, giving clear direction (important - player will have to follow it)",
                                          "checkflags": [],
                                          "setflags": [],
                                          "ruletags": [],
                                          "approval": [],
                                          "rolls": "",
                                          "goto": "",
                                          "link": "",
                                          "is_end": false,
                                          "node_type": "normal",
                                          "children": {
                                            "25": {
                                              "id": "25",
                                              "speaker": "Gale",
                                              "text": "Option two - black's king retreats up and right. Your knight can then move two squares left and one up to mate the king, your rook preventing his escape.",
                                              "context": "NodeContext: Knows exactly what he's talking about, giving clear direction (important - player will have to follow it)",
                                              "checkflags": [],
                                              "setflags": [
                                                "WYR_Chess_Knows_HeardGalesSolution"
                                              ],
                                              "ruletags": [],
                                              "approval": [],
                                              "rolls": "",
                                              "goto": "",
                                              "link": "",
                                              "is_end": true,
                                              "node_type": "normal",
                                              "children": {}
                                            }
                                          }
                                        }
                                      }
                                    },
                                    "7": {
                                      "id": "7",
                                      "speaker": "Gale",
                                      "text": "First, the white queen moves up and right, diagonally, two squares. This allows her to threaten black's king, while protected by her white knight.",
                                      "context": "NodeContext: Knows exactly what he's talking about, giving clear direction (important - player will have to follow it)",
                                      "checkflags": [],
                                      "setflags": [],
                                      "ruletags": [],
                                      "approval": [],
                                      "rolls": "",
                                      "goto": "",
                                      "link": "",
                                      "is_end": false,
                                      "node_type": "normal",
                                      "children": {
                                        "4": {
                                          "id": "4",
                                          "speaker": "Gale",
                                          "text": "The king will have no choice but to take the knight, ensnaring himself him between his own pawn and bishop. The white queen can then checkmate by moving one more square up and to the right.",
                                          "context": "NodeContext: Knows exactly what he's talking about, giving clear direction (important - player will have to follow it)",
                                          "checkflags": [],
                                          "setflags": [
                                            "WYR_Chess_Knows_HeardGalesSolution"
                                          ],
                                          "ruletags": [],
                                          "approval": [],
                                          "rolls": "",
                                          "goto": "",
                                          "link": "",
                                          "is_end": true,
                                          "node_type": "normal",
                                          "children": {}
                                        }
                                      }
                                    }
                                  }
                                },
                                "17": {
                                  "id": "17",
                                  "speaker": "Player",
                                  "text": "Sorry, but I'd rather think this one through on my own.",
                                  "context": "",
                                  "checkflags": [],
                                  "setflags": [],
